claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table comparing percentages of solicited local (pain, redness, firmness/swelling) and systemic (fatigue, headache, muscle pain, joint pain, shivers/chills, nausea, fever) adverse events of Flublok (N=1078) versus IIV3 (N=1081), stratified by any, moderate, and severe events. does not support the claim because the table only presents safety/adverse event data and contains no information on antigenic match or reference to WHO- or FDA-selected influenza strains. Note: The image quality is sufficient to identify contents; however, no antigenic or strain-match information is present.
